# LLM functions: naming

Functions that call OpenAI (Agents SDK, Realtime, etc.) are slow and cost money. **Signal that in the function name** so maintainers spot them in code review and call graphs — not in user-facing JSDoc.

Follow normal `jsdoc-usage.mdc` for comments (importers/call sites; do not litter docs with billing or “paid API” language).

## Naming

- Agent entry points: **`askLlmTo…`** (e.g. `askLlmToIdentifyLessonIntent`, `askLlmToIdentifyInterests`).
- Shared Agents SDK wrapper: **`askAgentAndLog`** in `lib/ask-agent.ts`.
- Include **agent or orchestrator** in the name when it is not already `askLlmTo…` (e.g. `askLlmToIdentifyRelevantAgent`, not `runOrchestrator`).
- Avoid vague verbs alone (`run`, `invoke`, `execute`, `fetch`) for LLM entry points.
- Logging is a side effect: **`somethingAndLog`**, not `loggedSomething`.

## Do not

- Put “paid”, “slow”, “costs tokens”, or similar in JSDoc — keep that in this rule for agents only.
- Scatter `OPENAI_API_KEY` checks — validate at process entry.

## Examples

| Function | Notes |
|----------|--------|
| `askAgentAndLog` | All Agents SDK agents |
| `askLlmToIdentifyRelevantAgent` | `reception-orchestrator-agent` |
| `askLlmToIdentifyLessonIntent` | `identify-lesson-intent-agent` |
| `askLlmToGenerateLesson` | `generate-lesson-agent` |
| `askLlmToIdentifyInterests` | `interests-observer-agent` |
